cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to extract data from clinical notes in mental health care electronic health records. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP and related areas. The use of SemEHR, a tool for clinical NLP, also suggests that the paper may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the application of machine learning techniques to healthcare data. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to extract data from electronic health records, which suggests that it may belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper may belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the use of technology in healthcare and its impact on society. Finally, the paper may belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it involves the use of technology to improve healthcare services for individuals with severe mental illness.
